<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-51-0234 </DOCNO><TEXT>The instantaneous post-decay output important for cooling in accidentsis obtained as the sum of the post-decay outputs of the fuel elements.Their burn-up is determined from the measurement of neutron flux densityrepeated at intervals of time. In this determination, the method of operationand positon of the fuel elements in the core can be taken into account.The post-decay output is displayed in the powerstation control room.</TEXT></DOC>